<section class="member-post--summary"><p>I am pleased to announce that the first milestone of Spring Batch 4.2 has been released and is available from our <a href="https://repo.spring.io/milestone/">milestone repository</a>.</p>
<p>The major feature of this release is the addition of batch metrics with <a href="https://micrometer.io">Micrometer</a>.</p>
<h2><a href="#batch-metrics-with-micrometer" class="anchor" name="batch-metrics-with-micrometer"></a>Batch Metrics with Micrometer</h2>
<p>This release introduces a new feature that lets you monitor your batch jobs by using Micrometer. By default, Spring Batch collects metrics (such as job duration, step duration, item read and write throughput, and others) and registers them in Micrometer’s global metrics registry under the <code>spring.batch</code> prefix. These metrics can be sent to any <a href="https://micrometer.io/docs/concepts#_supported_monitoring_systems">monitoring system</a> supported by Micrometer.</p>
</section>
